        <h2>What kind (breed) of horse do you like the most?</h2>

        <p>I love all kinds of horses. I think it's very important to find a breed that fits your own personality. I've been riding for many years, and I've tried many different horses. For me, it always comes out the same: I very much like the Warmblooded horses' temperament. They give me something to work with, and that's what I really enjoy.</p>


        <h2>Do you still have Bella?</h2>

        <p>In Denmark there is a rule that says you can't ride ponies at competitions after you turn 16 years old. She likes to work and loves to jump, so it was better for her to be somewhere else. Bella is now with a little boy, and they have so much fun together!</p>

        <p>I miss Bella a lot, but it was the right thing to do.</p>

        
        <h2>Do you ride dressage or jumping?</h2>

        <p>I have two young horses, so mostly I ride dressage. I do love to jump, though! I like the way you and the horse have to be in total control and work together to make it happen.</p>

        <p>The horses like to do something different from time to time, and it's very important to me that my horses are happy.</p>

